<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN230-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – atu. tuṟai – kaiyaṟunilai. atiyamāṉ takaṭurpotutuvīḻnta eḻaṉiyai aricilkiḻār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN230">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kaṉṟama rāyaṅ kāṉat talkavum</l>
<l>veṅkāl vampalar vēṇṭupulat tuṟaiyavuṅ</l>
<l>kaḷamali kuppai kāppila vaikavum</l>
<l>vilaṅkupakai kaṭinta kalaṅkāc ceṅkōl</l>
<l>vaiyakam pukaḻnta vayaṅkuviṉai yoḷvāṭ</l>
<l>poyyā veḻiṉi porutukaḷañ cēra</l>
<l>vīṉṟō ṇītta kuḻavi pōlat</l>
<l>taṉṉamar cuṟṟan talaittalai yiṉaiyak</l>
<l>kaṭumpaci kalakkiya viṭumpaikūr neñcamoṭu</l>
<l>nōyuḻantu vaikiya vulakiṉu mikanaṉi</l>
<l>nīyiḻan taṉaiyē yaṟaṉiṟ kūṟṟam</l>
<l>vāḻtaliṉ varūum vayalvaḷa ṉaṟiyāṉ</l>
<l>vīḻkuṭi yuḻavaṉ vittuṇ ṭāaṅ</l>
<l>koruva ṉāruyi ruṇṇā yāyi</l>
<l>ṉērār palluyir paruki</l>
<l>yārkuvai maṉṉōvava ṉamaraṭu kaḷattē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While the cows desired by [their] calves remain in the forest, (1)</l>
<l>while hot-legged travellers stay in the places they want, (2)</l>
<l>while the ample heaps on the threshing flooe are kept without guard, (3)</l>
<l>as falseless Eḻiṉi after fighting joined the battle field, (6)</l>
<l>with [his] just sceptre unperturbed that had chased away bothersome enemies, (4)</l>
<l>with [his] bright sword of glowing work[manship] that was praised by the world, (5)</l>
<l>while his battle troups despair one by one, (8)</l>
<l>like a calf that was left by her who bore it, (7)</l>
<l>very much more than the world which is kept enduring pain, (10)</l>
<l>with hearts abounding in distress when afflicted with fierce hunger, (9)</l>
<l>you are lost, virtueless Death. (11)</l>
<l>If, like a ploughman of a sunken clan who does not know </l>
<l>the wealth of strength that comes from living (12f.)</l>
<l>you don’t eat the precious life of one man, (14)</l>
<l>will you drink up the many lives of the enemies (15)</l>
<l>[and] be satiated, on the battle field where he abides? (16)</l>
</lg>
